Maspeth Ave. (left), east from about 54th Street to 58th Street, showing in the background south of Maspeth Ave. on the east side of 58th Street, from left to right, the Queens Head Tavern, at the corner, the Maurice house, in the center, and the Episcopal Church of St. Saviours. Across this view are also shown the tracks and right of way of the Long Island Railroad.

March 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

Maspeth Ave., (left), east from about 54th to 58th Street, showing in the background south of Maspeth Ave., on the east side of 58th Street, from left to right, the Queens Head Tavern, at the corner; the Maurice house, in the center; and the Episcopal Church of St. Saviours. Across this view are also seen the tracks and right of way of the Long Island Railroad.

About March 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(1) Maspeth Ave., west from about 54th Street, showing a westward view of Furman's Island; which was in 1929 a part of Queens County mainland. In the background is seen smoke stacks and a gas tank on the King's County side.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2) The same, showing a close up of the background seen in View No. 1. This view was taken from about 48th Street.

Eugene L. Armbruster.
September 1929.
